umb towards door A-1. Krug entered; Frau Doktor von Wytwyl née Bachofen (the third, eldest, sister) was gently, almost dreamily, shaking a thermometer as she looked down at the bed near which she stood in the far corner of the room. Then she turned to Krug and advanced towards him.

'Brace yourself,' she said quietly. 'There has been an accident. We have done our best —'

